Occurrence: Mediterranean Sea and northeast Atlantic, from Ireland ( Mortensen 1927a ), along the coast of Europe ( Nobre 1938 ) to Mauritania ( Chapman 1955 ), including the archipelagos of the Azores (Marques 1989), Madeira (
Alves et al . 2001
), Selvagens (
Pérez-Ruzafa et al. 2002
), Canaries (
Pérez-Ruzafa et al. 2003
) and Cape Verde (
Pérez-Ruzafa et al. 1999
).

Habitat:
preferentially rocky shores where it can bore holes in the rock (
Schultz 2006
); diet mainly of algae (
Mortensen 1943a
).
